## Resilience Patterns

### Local Filesystem Fallback

External services (MinIO, Redis) may be unavailable. Implement local fallback.

```python
class ResilientStorage:
    def __init__(self, remote_client, local_path: Path):
        self._remote = remote_client
        self._local = local_path
        self._local.mkdir(parents=True, exist_ok=True)

    def save(self, key: str, data: bytes) -> bool:
        try:
            self._remote.put(key, data)
            return True
        except Exception as e:
            logger.warning("Remote save failed, using local: %s", e)

        local_path = self._local / key
        local_path.write_bytes(data)
        return True
```

