## Fire-and-Forget Async Pattern

For parallel processing that must not add latency to the main path:

```python
import asyncio

async def process_shadow(action):
    try:
        await asyncio.wait_for(shadow_service.evaluate(action), timeout=5.0)
    except asyncio.TimeoutError:
        logger.warning("Shadow processing timed out")

# In main path:
asyncio.create_task(process_shadow(action))  # Does not block caller
```
